PROJECT: ~/_projects/popcorn-harness
This is a cross-platform skill/plugin that assembles execution harnesses on-the-fly.
It targets Claude Code (plugin), Hermes/Fox, and OpenClaw.

STRUCTURE:
  package.json                          # Claude Code plugin manifest
  README.md                             # install + usage guide
  commands/popcorn.md                   # /popcorn slash command
  agents/popcorn-orchestrator.md        # orchestrator agent persona
  skills/popcorn-harness/
    SKILL.md                            # main skill (cross-platform entry point)
    scripts/detect-platform.sh          # outputs JSON: platform detection
    scripts/discover-capabilities.sh    # outputs JSON: skills+agents+commands
    references/tier-decision-tree.md    # tier selection logic + edge cases
    references/assembly-patterns.md     # execution graph + parallel dispatch
    agents/popcorn-critic.md            # post-execution red-team reviewer

YOUR TASK — iterate until ALL of the following pass:

## 1. CORNER CASE AUDIT
Review every instruction in SKILL.md and all sub-files. For each step, ask:
- What happens if this fails silently?
- What if the user is on Windows (no bash)?
- What if claude agents command does not exist?
- What if available_skills is empty in Hermes?
- What if the user selects 0 capabilities after pruning?
- What if a subagent times out mid-execution?
- What if the task description is a single word?
- What if the user says "adjust" at Tier 2 prompt — what exactly happens?
Fix every gap found.

## 2. SCRIPT STABILITY
For each script in scripts/:
- Test it actually runs without errors: bash scripts/detect-platform.sh && bash scripts/discover-capabilities.sh
- Verify JSON output is valid: pipe through python3 -m json.tool
- Check for unbound variable errors (set -u)
- Verify it handles missing tools gracefully (no hard exits on missing claude/agents/etc)
- Fix any issues found

## 3. CLAUDE CODE PLUGIN COMPATIBILITY
Check package.json against known Claude Code plugin conventions:
- Does the claudeCode field follow the correct schema?
- Are the skills/, agents/, commands/ directories in the right locations for Claude Code to auto-discover?
- Does commands/popcorn.md follow the correct frontmatter format?
- Does agents/popcorn-orchestrator.md follow the correct agent frontmatter (name, description with examples, model)?
- Cross-reference with real installed plugins at ~/.claude/plugins/cache/claude-plugins-official/
  to verify conventions match

## 4. HERMES / OPENCLAW COMPATIBILITY
- Does SKILL.md work without any shell execution (pure context-based)?
- Is the skill_view() loading pattern correctly documented?
- Are all cross-platform paths correctly handled?

## 5. RED-TEAM REVIEW
After fixing everything above, act as a harsh critic:
- Grade the entire plugin A+ / A / B / C
- If not A+, identify remaining gaps and fix them
- Repeat until A+

## 6. COMMIT DISCIPLINE
- Each logical fix gets its own commit with a clear message
- Use conventional commits: fix:, feat:, docs:, refactor:
- Final state must be clean (git status shows nothing)

## COMPLETION PROMISE
When ALL of the following are true, output exactly "COMPLETE":
1. scripts/detect-platform.sh runs and outputs valid JSON
2. scripts/discover-capabilities.sh runs and outputs valid JSON
3. Every corner case identified has a documented handling in SKILL.md or sub-files
4. Claude Code plugin structure matches conventions from ~/.claude/plugins/cache/claude-plugins-official/
5. Red-team self-review gives A+
6. All changes are committed --agent claude-code --max-iterations 10 --completion-promise COMPLETE --no-commit
